<subSubSection id="C34C655AFFB253422604FE855B96BA91" pageId="3" pageNumber="434" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BE936D1FFB253422604FE855B96BA91" blockId="3.[825,1418,290,716]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
<emphasis id="B922EAC3FFB253422604FE855B6CBA32" bold="true" box="[826,1106,290,323]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 280-290 mm, ear 50 mm, hindfoot 46-50 mm; weight 700-725 g. Greatest lengths of skull are 63-69 mm. Back of the Sacha Guinea Pig is dark reddish drown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34C655AFFB253422604FE405CE3B9D5" pageId="3" pageNumber="434" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8BE936D1FFB253422604FE405CE3B9D5" blockId="3.[825,1418,290,716]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
<emphasis id="B922EAC3FFB253422604FE405C97B979" bold="true" box="[826,937,487,520]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Habitat.</emphasis>
High-elevation paramo in Ecuador at elevations of 3000-3800 m (type locality). This area has marshy areas and grassy slopes, with some forests of Polylepus (
<taxonomicName id="4C564D52FFB253422679FD205CEEB9D5" box="[839,976,647,676]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="3" pageNumber="434" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Rosaceae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34C655AFFB253422607FD0C5CA4B982" pageId="3" pageNumber="434" type="food_feeding">
